1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:03,710
A billionaire CEO just fired
over 4,000 employees and replaced

2
00:00:03,759 --> 00:00:07,070
their managers with AI. And
he says this is just

3
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:10,710
the beginning. Jack Dorsey, the
CEO of Block and co

4
00:00:10,759 --> 00:00:13,349
founder of Twitter, cut more
than 40% of his workforce

5
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:16,670
in February. But he says
this wasn't about the company

6
00:00:16,719 --> 00:00:20,469
struggling. It was a deliberate
bet on artificial intelligence. His

7
00:00:20,519 --> 00:00:24,350
argument is wild but simple.
He says managers basically exist

8
00:00:24,399 --> 00:00:27,839
to move information up and
down a chain. And now

9
00:00:27,890 --> 00:00:30,000
AI can do that through
a live world model of

10
00:00:30,050 --> 00:00:35,039
the entire business. Every decision,
every plan, every design already

11
00:00:35,090 --> 00:00:37,840
lives as a digital record.
So why do you need

12
00:00:37,890 --> 00:00:41,479
a human middleman? Now every
employee at Block falls into

13
00:00:41,530 --> 00:00:45,039
one of three builders who
make things, problem owners who

14
00:00:45,090 --> 00:00:49,159
drive outcomes and player coaches
who develop talent. No traditional

15
00:00:49,210 --> 00:00:53,500
managers. AI is the org
chart. If this works, every

16
00:00:53,549 --> 00:00:55,979
company in the world is
going to copy it. The

17
00:00:56,030 --> 00:00:59,820
question is, does your job
survive that shift? Follow for

18
00:00:59,869 --> 00:01:00,149

more.
